The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Lucknow (PTI): Former BJP MP Luxmi Narain Tripathi and his driver were shot dead by unidentified gunmen at his Vikas Nagar residence here on Sunday, police said.

 Three armed men entered Tripathis home on some pretext and opened indiscriminate fire. The former MP and his driver were seriously injured, the police said. Tripathi was rushed to hospital where he was declared brought dead. The driver succumbed to injuries a while later. 

 Madurai (PTI): J. Varadharajan put on 58 socks on his right leg to make it to the Guinness Book of World Records. The 22-year-old from Ramanathapuram, 130 km from here, has beaten Lara Mandy of London, who holds the record for wearing 50 socks. 

 Ajmer (PTI): A passenger train will be introduced between Ajmer and Agra on July 1 for the convenience of tourists and pilgrims. This has been made possible after metre-gauge tracks were converted to broad-gauge between Bandikui and Agra. Passengers from Ajmer now travel to Jaipur to reach Agra. 

 Ahmedabad (PTI): A man and his wife have been arrested following their 15-year-old nieces complaint that the man had raped her twice with her aunts assistance. Mohan and Rekha Mistri had taken the girl on a religious tour in April and had put up in dharamshalas where she was raped. 

 New Delhi (PTI): Vice-President Bhairon Singh Shekhawat, who had been 

suffering from cramps in his right leg, underwent minor surgery at the All India 

Institute of Medical Sciences on Sunday. There was a minor block in the 

blood vessels which has been successfully removed through a minor surgery. He 

is expected to be discharged from the hospital by tomorrow, an official 

spokesman said. 




